ch\":\"fix/update-command-mise-detection\",\"slug\":\"snuggly-frolicking-cray\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_018N9SzM1pffs4ycLkT24Z4V\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Web search results for query: \\\"aqua registry mise tool manager what is it\\\"\\n\\nLinks: [{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Aqua Backend | mise-en-place\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://mise.jdx.dev/dev-tools/backends/aqua.html\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Registry | mise-en-place\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://mise.jdx.dev/registry.html\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Automated Dependency Updates for mise-en-place - Renovate Docs\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://docs.renovatebot.com/modules/manager/mise/\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Dev Tools | mise-en-place\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://mise.jdx.dev/dev-tools/\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Backend Architecture | mise-en-place\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://mise.jdx.dev/dev-tools/backend_architecture.html\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Own Aqua Registry · jdx/mise · Discussion #4581\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/jdx/mise/discussions/4581\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"aqua-registry - crates.io: Rust Package Registry\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://crates.io/crates/aqua-registry\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Custom asdf registry · jdx/mise · Discussion #2435\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/jdx/mise/discussions/2435\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plugins | mise-en-place\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://mise.jdx.dev/plugins.html\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"What's the point of Mise over ASDF or Aqua? · jdx/mise · Discussion #2441\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/jdx/mise/discussions/2441\\\"}]\\n\\nBased on the search results, here's what the Aqua registry and its integration with mise is:\\n\\n## What is the Aqua Registry in mise?\\n\\nThe aqua registry is a collection of YAML files that get compiled into the mise binary on release. The aqua CLI is not used in mise at all.\\n\\n## How It Works with mise\\n\\nThe aqua backend gives access to almost all programs available on GitHub and offers the most features and security while not requiring plugins. The aqua registry is used to install tools from the aqua registry, and if a custom registry URL is set, the baked-in aqua registry is not used.\\n\\n## Security Features\\n\\nThe aqua backend supports multiple security verification methods to ensure the integrity and authenticity of downloaded tools, and mise provides native Rust implementation for all verification methods, eliminating the need for external CLI tools.\\n\\n## Key Benefits\\n\\nAqua is preferred to GitHub as it has better UX and more features like SLSA verification and the ability to use different logic for older versions. Setting symlink_bins = true creates a filtered bin directory containing symlinks only to the binaries explicitly defined in the aqua registry, preventing bundled dependencies from being exposed.\\n\\nIn summary, the Aqua registry is a centralized collection of tool definitions that mise uses to install and manage development tools with enhanced security and features compared to other backends.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"e47bdf55-1244-4085-ae2c-7350cfcd1fa7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T11:49:11.478Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"query\":\"aqua registry mise tool manager what is it\",\"results\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"srvtoolu_01Wc6mjND5tcp6nuNFdpfMhg\",\"content\":[{\"title\":\"Aqua Backend | mise-en-place\",\"url\":\"https://mise.jdx.dev/dev-tools/backends/aqua.html\"},{\"title\":\"Registry | mise-en-place\",\"url\":\"https://mise.jdx.dev/registry.html\"},{\"title\":\"Automated Dependency Updates for mise-en-place - Renovate Docs\",\"url\":\"https://docs.renovatebot.com/modules/manager/mise/\"},{\"title\":\"Dev Tools | mise-en-place\",\"url\":\"https://mise.jdx.dev/dev-tools/\"},{\"title\":\"Backend Architecture | mise-en-place\",\"url\":\"https://mise.jdx.dev/dev-tools/backend_architecture.html\"},{\"title\":\"Own Aqua Registry · jdx/mise · Discussion #4581\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jdx/mise/discussions/4581\"},{\"title\":\"aqua-registry - crates.io: Rust Package Registry\",\"url\":\"https://crates.io/crates/aqua-registry\"},{\"title\":\"Custom asdf registry · jdx/mise · Discussion #2435\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jdx/mise/discussions/2435\"},{\"title\":\"Plugins | mise-en-place\",\"url\":\"https://mise.jdx.dev/plugins.html\"},{\"title\":\"What's the point of Mise over ASDF or Aqua? · jdx/mise · Discussion #2441\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jdx/mise/discussions/2441\"}]},\"Based on the search results, here's what the Aqua registry and its integration with mise is:\\n\\n## What is the Aqua Registry in mise?\\n\\nThe aqua registry is a collection of YAML files that get compiled into the mise binary on release. The aqua CLI is not used in mise at all.\\n\\n## How It Works with mise\\n\\nThe aqua backend gives access to almost all programs available on GitHub and offers the most features and security while not requiring plugins. The aqua registry is used to install tools from the aqua registry, and if a custom registry URL is set, the baked-in aqua registry is not used.\\n\\n## Security Features\\n\\nThe aqua backend supports multiple security verification methods to ensure the integrity and authenticity of downloaded tools, and mise provides native Rust implementation for all verification methods, eliminating the need for external CLI tools.\\n\\n## Key Benefits\\n\\nAqua is preferred to GitHub as it has better UX and more features like SLSA verification and the ability to use different logic for older versions. Setting symlink_bins = true creates a filtered bin directory containing symlinks only to the binaries explicitly defined in the aqua registry, preventing bundled dependencies from being exposed.\\n\\nIn summary, the Aqua registry is a centralized collection of tool definitions that mise uses to install and manage development tools with enhanced security and features compared to other backends.\"],\"durationSeconds\":6.703688459000026},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"9459df9a-e94c-440f-a701-2d1160045a09\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e47bdf55-1244-4085-ae2c-7350cfcd1fa7\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"30159aa1-626d-4de8-923a-317a4859bbc4\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"fix/update-command-mise-detection\",\"slug\":\"snuggly-frolicking-cray\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_019rwpnHxQ1mKxbBbzTmdn3M\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[Aqua](https://aquaproj.github.io/) is a CLI version manager (similar to mise itself). What's relevant here is that aqua maintains a **large, curated registry** of ~2,800+ CLI tools — each with YAML definitions specifying how to download the correct binary for each OS/architecture from GitHub Releases.\\n\\nMise **embeds the aqua registry directly** into its binary at build time. It doesn't use the aqua CLI at all — it just leverages the registry as a database of tool definitions. This is actually how mise knows how to install most GitHub-released CLI tools out of the box.\\n\\n**Why it matters for mise:**\\n- It's the **preferred backend** over raw GitHub Releases (`ubi`) because the aqua registry entries include richer metadata: checksums, SLSA verification, per-version download URL patterns, and explicit binary names.\\n- If a tool is in the aqua registry, `mise install <tool>` just works with no plugin or custom config needed.\\n\\n**So for getting `entire` installable via mise**, getting it added to the [aqua registry](https://github.com/aquaproj/aqua-registry) would be the cleanest path — mise would pick it up automatically.\\n\\nSources:\\n- [Aqua Backend | mise-en-place](https://mise.jdx.dev/dev-tools/backends/aqua.html)\\n- [Registry | mise-en-place](https://mise.jdx.dev/registry.html)\\n- [Backend Architecture | mise-en